title: Start
---
$c1: PhantomRoot is already biting into the gala cameras. Keep your voice low and your hands clean.

-> $c2: Silas Wren has to die before midnight.
    $c1: Then make the proof packet show he never saw the hand that killed him.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Who is already inside?
    $c1: Vale Nyx has the camera contacts. Juno Kade controls the security spine. Trust neither one without a timestamp.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Vale
---
$c1: Camera contacts are live. The gala sees what I blink at, so try not to make me flinch.

-> $c2: Silas Wren has to die before midnight.
    $c1: Then keep him in profile. Dead men with clean angles make cleaner evidence.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: What can you see from inside?
    $c1: Wren, two body shadows, one nervous waiter, and Juno pretending the cameras do not answer to her.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Silas
---
$c1: I know that look. Someone has mistaken distance for leverage.

-> $c2: Silas Wren has to die before midnight.
    $c1: People keep making appointments with my corpse. I keep disappointing them.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Who wants you alive?
    $c1: Fewer people than want me useful. Useful lasts longer.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Juno
---
$c1: The security spine is awake. Whether it is loyal depends on who asks and how politely.

-> $c2: Silas Wren has to die before midnight.
    $c1: Then you need a blind spot, not a sermon. I can sell you one minute.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Can Vale trust your feed?
    $c1: Vale can trust timestamps. People are where things get expensive.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Close
---
$c1: Remote does not mean safe. It just means the consequences arrive wearing someone else's face.
===
